17/10/2008
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Interior ministers from Southeast European countries agreed to boost co-operation Thursday (October 16th) in the fight against organised crime and corruption, Slovenian Interior Minister Dragutin Mate said. 
Conferees reached agreement during the 8th regional ministerial conference on illegal migration, organised crime, corruption and terrorism, which opened on Thursday in the Slovenian town of Brdo pri Kranju. 
The main goals are to exchange solid practices in the field of counterterrorism and to further boost co-operation among police forces. 
(STA, B92, BTA - 16/10/08)
